-- Zambia Produced 750,000 Tons of Copper Last Year, Minister Says
-- B y   M i k e   C o h e n
-- 2011-02-09T12:19:18Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-09/zambia-produced-750-000-tons-of-copper-last-year-less-than-bank-estimated.html
Zambia produced about 750,000 metric
tons of copper last year, Mines Minister Maxwell Mwale said at
the Mining Indaba conference in  Cape Town  today.  The country’s central bank had previously estimated that
Zambia,  Africa ’s largest copper miner, had produced about
820,000 tons last year, citing provisional data.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Mike Cohen in Cape Town at 
 mcohen21@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
